The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Calcutta: Taxi driver Ramu Yadav was arrested on Monday night after a couple brought charges of misbehaviour against him at Lake police station.           
	Tathagata Banerjee, a filmmaker, and wife Nibedita alleged that when they tried to hire Ramus taxi in front of South City mall, he refused to take them. When Tathagata insisted, the driver threw all their belongings out of the car and drove the taxi away with just Nibedita in it. Tathagata followed and stopped him near a traffic signal from where it was taken to the police station.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): A 58-year-old man was allegedly strangled by his servant and an accomplice at his home in Delhi on Sunday night. Anil Sharma was found by his mother around 1.30am with a bed sheet around his neck and his limbs tied. Sankar Thapa, who had been with the family for a year, has gone missing. No police verification was done on Thapa.                  
	Thrissur (PTI): Kerala Assembly Speaker Lonappan Nambadan and others complained of irritation, swelling and itchiness in the eyes and had to see doctors after attending an event here on Monday. Police suspect the discomfort was caused by rays from powerful lights used at the function. The equipment were said to be defective and the contractor has been arrested.                  
	Mumbai (PTI): Marathi actor Vihang Nayak died in Navi Mumbai on Monday after his sports utility vehicle skidded off the road on hitting a divider. He had acted in several Hindi, Marathi and English films. The actor also featured in advertisements and Marathi television.                   
	Jammu (PTI): Two villagers were injured by a leopard in Jammu and Kashmir on Monday, sources said. The leopard attacked Skinder Kumar and Kewel Krishen in Jamola village. They were rescued by other villagers and taken to hospital.                  
	 Sanga Reddy (PTI): Five members of a family were killed and three seriously injured when their vehicle rammed into a stationary truck in Andhra Pradesh on Monday, police said.                                                                                                                         
